olive oil
1 carrot
1 celery
1 leek
1 packet chicken drumsticks
1 tbs plain flour
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1.75 cup boiling water
2 potato
20 g butter
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 bag parsley
1 packet Mild Chorizo

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Boil the kettle.
• Roughly chop carrot and celery. Thinly slice leek. Roughly chop mild chorizo.
• In a large bowl, combine chicken drumsticks, the plain flour and a pinch of salt and pepper.

• Heat a large ovenproof pot with a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken in batches, until golden, 3-4 minutes each side.
• Add carrot, celery, leek, Aussie spice blend, chicken style-stock powder, the boiling water (11/3 cups for 2 people / 31/2 cups for 4 people) and a pinch of pepper. Stir to combine.
• Cover pot with a lid or tightly with foil. Bake for 30 minutes.
• Remove foil, then bake, uncovered, for a further 20-25 minutes.
• In the last 15 minutes, add chorizo to the pot. Roast until lightly browned and cooked through.

TIP: The chicken will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• When the chicken and chorizo have 10 minutes remaining, peel potato, then cut into large chunks.
• Place potato in a large microwave-safe bowl. Cover with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave potato on high until tender, 6-7 minutes.
• Add the butter to the potato and season with salt. Mash until smooth.

Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help mash the potatoes!

• Divide cheats potato mash between bowls.
• Top with braised chicken drumsticks and chorizo. Spoon over any remaining pan sauce.
• Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!